This problem often occurs with `Kotlin` as well.
It would be more useful if other cases could be handled without additional reflection by `Kotlin`, for example

```java
   private final boolean isFoo;
   private final Boolean isBar;
   private final String baz-baz;

   public final boolean isFoo() {
      return this.isFoo;
   }

   @Nullable
   public final Boolean isBar() {
      return this.isBar;
   }

   @NotNull
   public final String getBaz-baz() {
      return this.baz-baz;
   }
```
